data.text: BLACK HISTORY MONTH PROFILE (DAY 24)(FAMILY DAY)(IN HONOR OF MY FATHER'S BIRTHDAY)(3 of 3):My Great-Aunt Patricia Belcher(born 1954) is an American film and television actress, best known for her role as attorney Caroline Julian on Bones. She also appeared in the film Jeepers Creepers as a psychic. She currently stars as the snobbish neighbor Mrs. Dabney in Good Luck Charlie. She is also known for her role of Janet S. Crotum on TV comedy: Better Off Ted.She became my great-aunt on June 3,1980. Prior to becoming an actress, Aunt Patricia appeared as a contestant on Jeopardy! losing to then attorney Ron Black in one of his 5 games.Aunt Patricia s one of the most active actors appearing in commercials. Products include GEICO, Staples and Time Warner, as well as for the American Cancer Society.Aunt Patricia has made many appearances in films, including The Number 23, Unknown, Jeepers Creepers, Heartbreakers and in 2009, (500) Days of Summer. She also has made appearances in television series, including Everybody Loves Raymond, Boston Legal, The Jake Effect,Twins, The Proud Family, Sister, Sister, In Plain Sight, and Still Standing "Beverly Hills, 90210". Aunt Patricia produced her 2008 role in the film Lower Learning as Colette. She had a cameo role in the second season of How I Met Your Mother, as the receptionist at the casino's wedding chappel in Atlantic City, and in the TV series Community as a cafeteria worker. Ant Patricia has a recurring role as attorney Caroline Julian on Bones as well as a recurring role on Disney Channel 's Good Luck Charlie as the Duncan family's neighbor, Mrs. Dabney She also appeared on Emily Owens, M.D. She has also made an appearance on the popular show Sabrina, the Teenage Witch as a science teacher.My Great-Aunt Patricia Belcher(born 1954) is an American film and television actress, best known for her role as attorney Caroline Julian on Bones.
